cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.EM, cs.ES

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a novel timing model for voltage over scaled (VoS) logic circuits, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of circuit design. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper presents a case study of a two point DFT unit employing the proposed model, which can be considered an architectural design. 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper deals with the timing distribution of output bits in digital circuits, which falls under the scope of cs.DC. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper mentions the use of an error-injector, which can be considered an electromagnetic phenomenon. 
- cs.ES (Embedded Systems): The paper proposes a model that can be used to represent erroneous VoS circuits as error-free circuits combined with an error-injector, which can be considered an embedded system design.
